/- The opposite of a morphism in `C`. -/
@[hott, reducible]
def hom_op [has_hom.{v} C] {x y : C} (f : x ‚ü∂ y) : op y ‚ü∂ op x := f
/- Given a morphism in `C·µí·µñ`, we can take the "unopposite" back in `C`. -/
@[hott]
